
  <sn><md>#### Roman Civilization

The Roman Civilization

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-9
Although most ancient civilizations developed around rivers, the `Roman Civilization` was not river-based. It developed around the small city of `Rome`, located in the western part of Italy. A group of Indo-European people settled in `Northern Italy` around `2000 BC`. Their language was `Latin`. Over time, it became widely known as the `Latin language`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-3
![img](https://media.gettyimages.com/id/1491504743/vector/the-colosseum-in-rome-italy-1859.jpg?s=612x612\&amp;w=0\&amp;k=20\&amp;c=QrUyjiE0_UNY9JE7hglbVGWeIApTmUQTMOBLEiY3K5Y=)
:::

:::

The Latin king `Romulus` founded a city. The city was named Rome after its founder.

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
Rome's economy was heavily dependent on `slave labor`. Slaves were subjected to inhumane treatment. Eventually, a major **Slave Revolt** took place under the leadership of a slave named `Spartacus`. The rebel slaves managed to survive in **Southern Italy** for **two years**. The revolt came to an end when Spartacus was killed in `71 BC`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-5
![img](https://cdn.thecollector.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/slavery-market-in-ancient-rome.jpg?width=2560\&amp;height=1440\&amp;quality=100\&amp;dpr=2)
:::

:::

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
The most famous emperor of Rome was `Julius Caesar`. He became the ruler of Rome in `46 BC`. His famous quote was, *"I came, I saw, I conquered."* However, as power struggles and conspiracies intensified in Rome, Julius Caesar was assassinated by two nobles named `Brutus` and `Cassius`.

Rome then became involved in a civil war. Eventually, three leaders came to power jointly: `Octavius Caesar`, `Mark Antony`, and `Lepidus`. Their collective rule is known in history as the `Triumvirate`. The Triumvirate did not last long.

Octavius Caesar first defeated Lepidus.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-5
![img](https://media.gettyimages.com/id/1756544360/photo/the-death-of-julius-caesar-gaius-julius-caesar-roman-politican-general-historian-100-bc-44-bc.jpg?s=612x612\&amp;w=0\&amp;k=20\&amp;c=sAeK6ADrl32-Dv44z6xaW7oV6KnlaE2ZbTlXyGrJDkY=)
:::

:::

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
Antony strengthened his position by marrying the Egyptian queen `Cleopatra`. Cleopatra is known in history as the `Serpent of the Nile`. However, she too was defeated by Octavius Caesar.

After becoming the sole ruler of the Roman Empire, Octavius Caesar adopted the title `Augustus Caesar`.

The most significant event during the reign of Augustus Caesar was the birth of `Jesus Christ`, the founder of Christianity. Augustus Caesar died in `AD 14`.

The Roman Empire finally fell in `AD 476`. The last Roman emperor was `Romulus Augustulus`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-5
![Img](https://media.gettyimages.com/id/475598285/photo/unspecified-the-death-of-mark-antony-by-pompeo-batoni-oil-on-canvas-76x100-cm-18th-century.jpg?s=612x612\&amp;w=0\&amp;k=20\&amp;c=UWJ8UudFromJXubBdm75GMPAeMJZy_gXJUSoTG9m0X4=)
:::

