<sn><md>#### Philosophy

The most popular philosophical doctrine in Rome was `Stoicism`. Three individuals played a major role in the development of this philosophy. They were the wealthy Roman `Seneca`, a former slave named `Epictetus`, and the Roman emperor `Marcus Aurelius`.

```id="t7k3pl"
Stoicism
        |
        +--&gt; Seneca
        |
        +--&gt; Epictetus
        |
        +--&gt; Marcus Aurelius
```
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Literature

The poets `Horace` and `Virgil` of the Augustan Age achieved great fame. Virgil's epic poem `Aeneid` has been translated into the Bengali language. `Ovid` and `Livy` were two other renowned literary figures of this period. The famous historian `Tacitus` wrote about the origins and history of Rome during this era.

```id="u5f9md"
Roman Literature
        |
        +--&gt; Horace
        |
        +--&gt; Virgil
        |       |
        |       +--&gt; Aeneid
        |
        +--&gt; Ovid
        |
        +--&gt; Livy
        |
        +--&gt; Tacitus
```
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Architecture and Sculpture

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
One of the most famous architectural monuments of Rome is the `Pantheon`, a temple built by `Emperor Hadrian`. Although the dome of the Pantheon was constructed nearly two thousand years ago, it still stands today as the world's `largest unreinforced concrete dome`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-5
![img](https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/pantheon-rome-frontal-view-front-italy-capital-city-ancient-gods-temple-famous-roman-classic-facade-colorful-sky-429339730.jpg)
:::

:::

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-5
![img](https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/colosseum-coliseum-isolated-on-white-260nw-1698652720.jpg)
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
The `Colosseum` was the largest amphitheater of the ancient world. It could accommodate up to `56,000 spectators` at one time.
:::

:::

```id="r4v1yb"
Architecture
        |
        +--&gt; Pantheon
        |       |
        |       +--&gt; Largest Dome
        |
        +--&gt; Colosseum
                |
                +--&gt; Amphitheater
                +--&gt; 56,000 Spectators
```
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Law

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-8
The greatest achievement of the Romans was in the field of `law`. The Byzantine emperor `Justinian` was the first to fully compile Roman law. Modern legal systems around the world are largely based on Roman law.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-4
![img](https://brewminate.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/100518-17-Ancient-History-Rome-Roman-Law-300x233.png)
:::

:::

```id="m8d2cn"
Roman Law
        |
        +--&gt; Justinian
                |
                +--&gt; Compilation of Roman Law
```
